Bushwaller's is one of my FAVORITE venues in downtown Frederick.🤩Through the years Bushwaller's has kept that  hometown feel, kinda like that bar in Boston 😉"where everyone knows your name"😉.  As Bushwaller's is a smaller venue, they do not take reservations. However, if you have a group of more than 6 people, call in advance and they'll do their best to accommodate seating for your party! The antique bar, the wall behind it, and the copper top smaller bar in the back are antiques. In conjunction with the staff they create a consistent warm and inviting atmosphere. While many other restaurants downtown are closed one day a week, usually Mondays, Bushwaller's is not! They usually have entertainment of some type 6 nites a week. This includes, aside from the great patrons, live music, karaoke, and trivia night. On Friday and Saturday nights they usually have live music. After 9 p.m. there is a cover charge. It is between $3 to $5 per person. When I've been there and they've had live music, I've always enjoyed the band.  Myself, I'm not a dart player, but they do have two dart boards 🙂 that attract many players. They have beer on tap with the system that was originally installed by Guinness! Who knows more about beer than Guinness! Well I'm not a whiskey drinker I understand their selection is top of the line and excellent in the choices they provide. The current owner, I only know her by her first name, Amber has done a fantastic job. The menu she has perfected presents a refined Irish / American selection. Her attention to excellence and detail~from the kitchen to the wait staff and ultimately the plate in front of your face is apparent from your very first bite. I favor the fish and chips and the bangers n mash. A great treat for Sunday brunch as well. No matter the night I've always found it's a great place to relax, have a drink and enjoy.

The fish and chips was cooked perfectly, just the right amount of crunch to the fish and the batter was thin so no doughy. Brandon set the fish down and said "I'll be right back with ketchup and malt vinegar," without me saying anything which is refreshing. I enjoyed the cocktail sauce as it was closer to an old bay remoulade vs the typical relish laiden sauce that can take away from a fish dish in my opinion. Definetly worth a stop if you are in, around, or driving through Fredrick, MD.

Took advantage of the Frederick Restaurant Week deals and decided to try this place since we drive past it quite often.  The crab pretzel was delicious - the crab dip on the top was really good!  My boyfriend had the Crab and Corn Chowder which had a spicy kick to it but he finished it.  For our entrees, I had the lobster macaroni and cheese (Restaurant week special) and he had the Dublin Dog.  The macaroni and cheese was good but a bit soupy for my taste.  He liked the Dublin Dog as well.  We were so full from the appetizers that we took half of our portions to go and the desserts to go as well (Irish Whiskey Cake and Strawberry Shortbread) that we have yet to try.  The atmosphere was very cozy and our waitress was very kind and attentive.  Two thumbs up!  Went again 4/13  So we visited Bushwaller's again on a busy Friday night and it was amazing!!  Even though it was very busy and crowded, the staff managed to find my boyfriend and I a table.  I ordered the crab pretzel which was so delicious that it may be my new favorite appetizer.  He ordered the crab and corn chowder which he said was satisfying as well.  For our entrees, he ordered the bangers and mash that he found very tasty but he had to box the rest.  I ordered the pot pie and it was also delicious!  The pastry to meat ratio was perfect - I also had to box it up.  Probably the absolutely best part was our server Liv!  She was so friendly and engaging!  My boyfriend's half-and-half drink was always replaced with a refill and she constantly checked on us despite the many other diners.  It's rare to find people in the service industry that are genuine and Liv really was!  We will definitely visit again soon!

Best place to go for live music. They almost always have a good (cover band) but they also have a lot of local original artists and bands that play venues and you can always play darts or enjoy the atmosphere. Frederickians are always pleasant and friendly people and most of the locals like to sit and talk outside of the bar during the summer if its too loud or crowded inside. Sitting on the benches outside and listening to the music is just about as enjoyable as entering the establishment. The drink prices are a little high with 11 dollar long islands but their drink specials are pretty good if you like beer. They have a wide array of liquors. I've never been the biggest fan of their menu, definitely more of a nightspot then the place you go to eat and you can almost always play darts. The bathroom stalls are kind of cramped but that's to be expected with the older down town Frederick night life.
Food was really good and the drinks were priced right. Band was outstanding. We like this place because it's not "a scene" but rather a down to earth bar that you can get good Irish food.
